## 🎯 The Problem DocuGuard Solves

Imagine you sign a contract and email it to someone. How do you **prove** later that the document wasn't changed after you signed it? Traditional methods fail:

| Traditional Method | Problem |
|---|---|
| Visual inspection | Can't detect subtle edits |
| File metadata (date modified) | Easy to fake |
| Comparing file sizes | Size can stay the same after edits |
| Watermarks | Can be removed or forged |

**DocuGuard's solution:** Cryptographic hashing — any change to the document, no matter how small, produces a completely different mathematical fingerprint.

