## 🔑 HMAC-SHA256 Explained

HMAC adds your secret key to the hash — so even if someone knows the algorithm, they can't fake a valid hash without your key.

```python
# Simplified HMAC formula:
ipad = 0x36 repeated 64 times
opad = 0x5C repeated 64 times

K_ipad = secret_key XOR ipad
K_opad = secret_key XOR opad

HMAC = SHA256(K_opad + SHA256(K_ipad + message))
```

```
Without secret key:
  Anyone can compute SHA256("contract.pdf bytes") = abc123
  But they CANNOT compute HMAC without your secret!

With HMAC, you get:
  Integrity  — file wasn't changed
  Authentication — came from this specific DocuGuard instance
```

