## 🌳 Merkle Tree Explained

Used to verify multiple documents with a single hash:

```
Step 1: Hash each document
  Doc1 → H1 = sha256(doc1)
  Doc2 → H2 = sha256(doc2)
  Doc3 → H3 = sha256(doc3)
  Doc4 → H4 = sha256(doc4)

Step 2: Pair and hash pairs
  H12 = sha256(H1 + H2)
  H34 = sha256(H3 + H4)

Step 3: Hash the pair-hashes
  ROOT = sha256(H12 + H34)

         [ROOT]
        /      \
    [H12]      [H34]
    /   \      /   \
  [H1] [H2] [H3] [H4]
  Doc1 Doc2 Doc3 Doc4

To verify Doc3 changed:
  Recompute H3' → H34' → ROOT'
  ROOT' ≠ ROOT → Doc3 was modified ✅
  Only need O(log n) hashes to verify!
```

