## 💥 Avalanche Effect Demonstration

This is WHY cryptographic hashing works for tamper detection:

```
Original:  "Contract signed by Alice on 2025-06-13 for $10,000"
SHA-256:   f3b9a2e1c8d7f4a0b5e3c9a8d2f7b1e4c6a9f3b8d5e2a7c4f1b6e9d3a8c5f2

Tampered:  "Contract signed by Alice on 2025-06-13 for $10,001"
SHA-256:   7a2c8f4e1b9d5a3c7f2e8a4c1b9d5f3e7a2c8f4e1b9d5a3c7f2e8a4c1b9d5f3
           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
           COMPLETELY DIFFERENT — only $1 changed but all 64 chars changed!
```

The probability of two different documents having the same SHA-256 hash is approximately **1 in 2²⁵⁶** — more atoms than exist in the observable universe.

