## 🗄️ Data Storage Design

DocuGuard stores ONLY fingerprints — never your documents:

```json
{
  "user_123456789": {
    "DG-96C568B3A93AC4093DCCAB2EFBEA17C": {
      "doc_id": "DG-96C568B3A93AC4093DCCAB2EFBEA17C",
      "file_name": "contract.pdf",
      "file_size": 245760,
      "mime_type": "application/pdf",
      "sha256": "a3f9c2e1b4d8f7a0c5e2b1d9f3a8c4e7...",
      "hmac": "7f2e8a1c9b4d5f3e7a2c8f4e1b9d5a3c...",
      "sha3_256": "b4d9f3c2a7e5b1d8c3f6a9e2b5d8c1f4...",
      "registered_by": "user_123456789",
      "registered_at": "2025-06-13T10:30:00Z",
      "username": "Aman"
    }
  }
}
```

**What's stored:** Hashes, filename, size, timestamp, who registered it
**What's NOT stored:** The actual file content — zero document bytes ever written to disk

